KATSINA – Members of the National Youth Service Corps, Medical and Health Team in Katsina Local Government Area have carried out a sensitization exercise on Intestinal worm infestation and dewormed 700 of Almajiris in Rafukka Community in the State. The program which took place on Thursday, witnessed a massive turnout of the Community members led by the Ward head, Alhaji Salisu Sani. The Almajiris were also given relief materials such as detergents, footwears, clothing, and plastic buckets by the Corps members. What You Need Know About Fertilisation Of Women’s Egg Third Dose Of AstraZeneca COVID-19 Vaccine Helps Against Delta… Speaking at the event, the President of the group, Abubakar Usman Dauda and his Deputy Samuel Esther, in their separate remarks, disclosed that they decided to carry out the activity in that community as part of their Community Development Service to assist the people. Similarly, they also used the occasion to educate the people and the Almajiris children on the importance of hygiene and good health According to them, they have observed over time that the majority of Almajiries dress in shabby clothes and move about barefooted and eat in between meals in a very unhealthy manner. “This was why, they thought it wise for them to be dewormed and get to know that a healthy environment is important to good living”. On his part, the State Coordinator NYSC Katsina State, Alhaji Ahidjo Yahaya appealed to the communities to always encourage Corps members to carry out projects that would benefit the community. POLL In his address, the Ward Head of the community, Alhaji Salisu Sani appreciated the Corps members for selecting the community for such a viable project and prayed Allah to protect them.